BAGHDAD : Prime Minister Nouri Al Maliki won the largest share of Iraqi parliamentary seats in last month 's national elections , dealing a blow to Shiite , Sunni and Kurdish rivals who opposed his serving a third term .

Preliminary results on Monday showed Maliki won at least 94 seats , far more than his two main Shiite rivals , the movement of Muqtada Sadr , which picked up 28 seats , and the Islamic Supreme Council of Iraq ( ISCI ) , which won 29 seats .
